# Project Tooling (comfort-b2b)

Yarn 4 (Berry) workspaces monorepo. Packages are scoped `@comfort-b2b/*`
(`shared`, `backend`, `mobile`). Always use `yarn`, never `npm`/`pnpm`.

## Definition of done
Before declaring ANY work complete, run `yarn check` from the repo root and make
it fully green. It runs: `typecheck` -> `lint` -> `knip` -> `test` -> `format:check`.
The Husky `pre-commit` hook runs the same `yarn check` (no lint-staged).

## Adding dependencies
Use `yarn add` / `yarn add -D` so versions resolve to latest and the lockfile
updates. Do not hand-write dependency versions in `package.json`.

## Pinned / non-obvious facts (do not "upgrade" without reason)
- ESLint pinned to v9 and `eslint-plugin-unicorn` to v56 (newer majors target
  ESLint 10, which the plugin ecosystem does not support yet).
- Config files are TypeScript: `eslint.config.ts` (loaded via `jiti`) and
  `jest.config.ts` (loaded natively by Jest 30 under Node type-stripping).
  There are NO `.js` / `.mjs` / `.cjs` files in the repo - keep it that way.
- New root-level `.ts` config/tooling files must be added to `tsconfig.json`
  `include` so `yarn typecheck` actually covers them (otherwise it's a blind spot).
- Node 22 is pinned via `.nvmrc` + `engines`; TS is strict
  (`noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`).
- Tests run via `@swc/jest`; node-modules linker (not PnP) for Metro/RN.
